# No frontend environment variables are required.
# - Download config is fetched from the GitHub Releases API at runtime
# - Download URLs use Netlify redirects
#
# Release/signing secrets do NOT belong in this file — they are not Vite env
# vars and are never shipped to the browser. They live in two places:
#
# 1. ./release.env           — consumed by deploy.sh on the mac release host
#                              (gitignored; template at ./release.env.example)
#
# 2. GitHub Actions secrets  — consumed by .github/workflows/build-windows.yml
#                              to sign the Windows updater bundle and patch
#                              latest.json. Configure in:
#                              Settings -> Secrets and variables -> Actions
#
#    Required GitHub Actions secrets:
#      TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY           (same value as in release.env)
#      TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD  (same value as in release.env)
#
# See ./release.env.example for the full list of signing/notarization vars
# and the exact gh CLI commands to mirror them as GitHub Actions secrets.
